description:
My roommate, cousin, and I waited an excruciating 1.5 hours on Friday at 7:00pm to dine at Loló. That was painful. Learn from our mistake and make a reservation in advance. Otherwise, you'll be hangry out of your mind when the menu arrives. And if you're anything like me and my delirious party, you too will end up over-ordering like starved hyenas.

In Filipino, "lolo" means grandfather. Yours would probably love to check this place out, and for good reason! Who doesn't enjoy a couple (or more) devilishly scrumptious Mexican tapas, while basking in a tropical-themed atmosphere? No sunscreen required.

// Taco Tropical ($11 / 2 pcs.) - 5 stars
I loved how unique the jicama tortillas were. They added a light and refreshing crunchiness to every bite of the taco. Throw in some fried shrimp with spicy aioli smothered on top, and you have yourself Loló's most popular dish.

// Tuna Tacon ($12 / 2 pcs.) - 4 stars
More Asian-fusion with the albacore tuna and avocado one-two punch. Overall very good, but I thought the tuna was a little dry.

// Calamary and Octopus Gorditas ($14 / 2 pcs.) - 4 stars
My cousin called this dish the "black mystery bread." I enjoyed it more than the other two did, but finishing an entire gordita was too heavy. I'd recommend splitting one piece with someone else.

// Grilled Octopus ($28) - 5 stars
The octopus was tender and had a pristinely clean texture. This was my favorite dish of the night.

// Carnitas ($18) - 4 stars
Particularly juicy and packed with flavor.

// Lamb Sliders ($12 / 2 pcs.) - 3 stars
The porcini mushroom sauce was excellent with its creaminess and earthy aftertaste. I thought the lamb was too overcooked though.

// Guacamole ($8) - 2 stars
Although I did like the cotija cheese, the consistency of the guacamole was lacking. It didn't have enough of an avocado oomph to it. None of us were fans of this appetizer.

ProTip: If you are an odd-numbered group and are eyeing a dish that comes in pieces of 2 (i.e. Taco Tropical, Tuna Tacon, etc.), you can request for just a single additional piece at half the cost of a regular order.
